text: “You about to lose yo job,” a months-old warning from a Black woman to the officer detaining her, has become the protest song of the moment. @skornhaber on how demonstrators are creating new political anthems: https://t.co/5iroPDODmy

text: “FDT,” this era’s signature protest song, attracted attention for its outrage against Donald Trump, @skornhaber writes. But the track’s co-writer, the late Nipsey Hussle, knew that through carefully crafted verses, the song's message could create unity. https://t.co/lXBcPKb44x

text: “She sniffed about the threshold for traces of cigarette-smoke ... she even invented an excuse for rummaging his drawers in the search for French novels and cards.” Read “A Granted Prayer,” a newly rediscovered, unpublished story by Edith Wharton: https://t.co/GOE2x0OsAr

name: TheAtlantic
text:
Pfizer has shared early results from its coronavirus-vaccine trial, which it says show that the vaccine is more than 90 percent effective.

In October, @sarahzhang outlined the vaccine approval process and warned that early results would not be definitive. https://t.co/c6jw0j46Bg
